Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper addresses the problem of estimating depth maps from RGB images, which is a common task in computer vision. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a fully convolutional architecture with residual learning, which is a popular technique in deep learning. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper presents a novel way to efficiently learn feature map up-sampling within the network, which can be seen as an AI-related problem. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as depth estimation is an important task in robotics, especially for autonomous navigation. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category as the paper mentions that the proposed model can run in real-time on images or videos, which is a multimedia-related application.
